dct_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Lodz, sheet P-14. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dct_description_sm: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Lodz, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 40-29, 40-30, 41-29, and 41-30, 1942. Road classification based on British intelligence reports, 1943.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
